nodes.title: Model links
widgets_values:
You can't mix GGUF MultiTalk with non-GGUF main model, but you can mix different GGUF Qtypes with eachother.

GGUF:

[https://huggingface.co/city96/Wan2.1-I2V-14B-480P-gguf/tree/main](https://huggingface.co/city96/Wan2.1-I2V-14B-480P-gguf/tree/main)

[https://huggingface.co/Kijai/WanVideo_comfy_GGUF/tree/main/InfiniteTalk](https://huggingface.co/Kijai/WanVideo_comfy_GGUF/tree/main/InfiniteTalk)

Fp8:

[https://huggingface.co/Kijai/WanVideo_comfy_fp8_scaled](https://huggingface.co/Kijai/WanVideo_comfy_fp8_scaled/tree/main/InfiniteTalk)

fp16:

[https://huggingface.co/Kijai/WanVideo_comfy/tree/main/InfiniteTalk](https://huggingface.co/Kijai/WanVideo_comfy/tree/main/InfiniteTalk)

Clip vision is not strictly necessary

Any I2V model should work, MAGREF can be interesting to play with as well.

nodes.title: Wav2vec2 safetensors
widgets_values:
Alternative to the download node is to use single .safetensors file from:

[https://huggingface.co/Kijai/wav2vec2_safetensors/tree/main](https://huggingface.co/Kijai/wav2vec2_safetensors/tree/main)

The model goes to `ComfyUI/models/wav2vec2`

nodes.title: Wav2vec2 safetensors
widgets_values:
Vocal separator model

[https://huggingface.co/Kijai/MelBandRoFormer_comfy/tree/main](https://huggingface.co/Kijai/MelBandRoFormer_comfy/tree/main)

The model goes to `ComfyUI/models/diffusion_models`

A confident western male presenter stands on a professional conference stage, facing the camera directly. 
He is wearing a dark navy suit, a white dress shirt, and a light blue tie, holding a handheld microphone close to his mouth. 
The man is speaking clearly and naturally, with subtle head movements and realistic mouth motion synchronized to speech. 
His facial expression is calm, friendly, and professional, as if delivering an opening speech to an audience. 
Soft cinematic lighting, shallow depth of field, blurred conference background, realistic proportions, high detail.

Close-up, bright tones, overexposed, static, blurred details, subtitles, style, works, paintings, images, static, overall gray, worst quality, low quality, JPEG compression residue, ugly, incomplete, extra fingers, poorly drawn hands, poorly drawn faces, deformed, disfigured, misshapen limbs, fused fingers, still picture, messy background, three legs, many people in the background, walking backwards

increase audio_scale for stronger effect

audio_cfg adds extra model pass for improved/stronger lipsync, default range is 3-5

num_frames is the maximum frame count to generate, if the value is higher than your audio length would be, the audio length is used

The model uses audio stride 2, meaning output fps is 16 while input audio fps is 32
Make sure the input audio duration is sufficient for all extension steps to avoid errors.
Make sure the input audio duration is sufficient for all extension steps to avoid errors.
If you are using a 2x Large or higher machine type, please set attention_mode to "sdpa".
If you are using a 2x Large or higher machine type, please set the attention_mode parameter in the WanVideo Model Loader node to "sdpa".
